<h2>Gluten-Free Dining Tips in Rehoboth Beach</h2>

<p>When dining out in Rehoboth Beach, it’s important to take a few precautions to ensure a safe gluten-free experience. Here are some tips to keep in mind:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Communicate with the Staff:</strong> Always inform your server about your gluten-free needs. Ask questions about how dishes are prepared and whether there’s a risk of cross-contamination.</li>
    <li><strong>Check Menus Online:</strong> Many restaurants in Rehoboth Beach have their menus available online, including gluten-free options. Reviewing the menu beforehand can help you make an informed decision.</li>
    <li><strong>Bring Your Own Snacks:</strong> If you’re unsure about the availability of gluten-free options, consider bringing your own snacks or gluten-free bread to supplement your meal.</li>
    <li><strong>Use Gluten-Free Apps:</strong> Apps like Find Me Gluten Free can help you locate gluten-free restaurants in the area and read reviews from other gluten-free diners.</li>
</ul>

